    <div class="intro-text">

              <h1 class="_title post-title">Scholarships and Awards</h1>
        
      
  
      <p class="_subtitle">Scholarships, Awards + Opportunities</p>
  
  <p>The Office of Scholarships at UIC focuses on campus based scholarships. These awards can be viewed on the <a href="http://scholarships.uic.edu/scholarships/uic-scholarships/">UIC scholarships</a> page.</p>
<p>Additionally, we receive information on a variety of other scholarships that may be helpful for UIC students. Most scholarships focus on specific disciplines, degrees, extracurricular activities or are for use during study abroad.</p>
<p>UIC undergraduate and professional school students interested in applying for nationally and internationally competitive scholarships, fellowships and external scholarship awards are encouraged to visit the <a href="http://oef.uic.edu/">Office of External Fellowships website.</a></p>
<p>UIC graduate students are encouraged to contact the Fellowships and Financial Aid Coordinator at the Graduate College. For more information related to funding for graduate degree programs or visit the <a href="http://grad.uic.edu/funding-your-education">Graduate College website</a>.</p>


</div>
    
    <div class="components">
  
</div>

